WEBVTT

00:00.334 --> 00:01.668
<i>Previously on</i>
<i>"Promised Land"...</i>

00:01.668 --> 00:02.794
[ Speaking Spanish ]

00:02.794 --> 00:07.674
♪♪

00:07.674 --> 00:07.716
I know it's in good hands.

00:08.842 --> 00:10.093
I know it's in good hands.

00:10.093 --> 00:11.428
♪♪

00:11.428 --> 00:13.096
What are you doing?
Come here.

00:13.096 --> 00:14.765
♪♪

00:14.765 --> 00:16.433
One phone call,
I can have you sitting

00:16.433 --> 00:18.477
in an ICE holding cell.

00:18.477 --> 00:20.020
Are you going to turn me in?

00:20.020 --> 00:22.147
I think about my father
on the day he died.

00:22.147 --> 00:24.525
And I blame you, Joe.

00:24.525 --> 00:25.859
Any idea who it might be?

00:25.859 --> 00:26.902
♪♪

00:26.902 --> 00:28.570
Oscar Mercer Honeycroft.

00:28.570 --> 00:30.113
This is my grandfather.

00:32.199 --> 00:40.207
♪♪

00:40.207 --> 00:43.210
[ Car door opens ]

00:46.338 --> 00:48.966
We have our smoking gun.

00:48.966 --> 00:51.802
Is that --
Your father's watch.

00:51.802 --> 00:53.136
Where did you get that?

00:53.136 --> 00:55.097
Some vineyard workers
were trenching.

00:55.097 --> 00:57.849
They found a skull
and a pile of buried bones.

00:57.849 --> 00:59.309
This was with them.

00:59.309 --> 01:01.311
♪♪

01:01.311 --> 01:03.313
Those rumors that Joe murdered
your father --

01:04.856 --> 01:06.233
they were true.

01:06.233 --> 01:09.319
♪♪

01:09.319 --> 01:10.946
Take me to him.

01:10.946 --> 01:14.199
♪♪

01:14.199 --> 01:15.534
Watch your step.

01:15.534 --> 01:23.333
♪♪

01:23.333 --> 01:24.376
They're gone.

01:24.376 --> 01:26.295
What?
The bones.

01:26.295 --> 01:27.337
They're gone.

01:27.337 --> 01:29.673
He must have moved them.

01:29.673 --> 01:30.757
Oh, son of a bitch.
Someone must have

01:30.757 --> 01:31.842
tipped off Joe.

01:31.842 --> 01:33.510
Well, without the bones,
we have nothing.

01:33.510 --> 01:36.013
Oh, no, no.
We --

01:36.013 --> 01:37.806
We still have the watch.

01:37.806 --> 01:38.849
It's not enough
to convict him,

01:38.849 --> 01:41.184
but think of the hit
to Joe's reputation.

01:41.184 --> 01:43.020
Think how many shareholders
will want to sell

01:43.020 --> 01:44.563
once he's under the cloud of
investigation,

01:44.563 --> 01:45.897
and you'll be right there
to buy them up.

01:45.897 --> 01:47.399
I slept next to that man
for 10 years.

01:47.399 --> 01:48.734
I had three
of his children.

01:48.734 --> 01:51.403
Joe Sandoval
is many things,

01:51.403 --> 01:52.988
but I can't believe
he's a killer.

01:52.988 --> 01:55.407
What, you think that I can
believe it?

01:55.407 --> 01:59.286
Joe hurt you.
I know.

01:59.286 --> 02:02.331
He hurt me, too.

02:02.331 --> 02:05.542
But this is not the way.

02:05.542 --> 02:08.628
So, he gets away, again?

02:08.628 --> 02:11.256
That's what you're saying?
I'm saying be patient.

02:11.256 --> 02:13.050
Let our plan
take its course.

02:13.050 --> 02:15.969
♪♪

02:15.969 --> 02:17.429
No.

02:17.429 --> 02:19.097
Not again.

02:19.097 --> 02:21.350
Reputation is everything
in this town.

02:21.350 --> 02:23.977
We're gonna give them
something to talk about.

02:23.977 --> 02:29.858
♪♪

02:29.858 --> 02:31.026
[ Sighs ]

02:34.029 --> 02:37.199
♪♪

02:37.199 --> 02:39.785
Mara: A few questions before
tonight's awards ceremony.

02:39.785 --> 02:42.371
Most people who enter
into the California Entrepreneur

02:42.371 --> 02:44.623
Hall of Fame are tech guys
in suits

02:44.623 --> 02:47.417
who give me tours
of their conference rooms.

02:47.417 --> 02:48.919
This is breathtaking.

02:48.919 --> 02:50.879
My job has more suits
and conference rooms

02:50.879 --> 02:52.589
than it used to.
[ Chuckles ]

02:52.589 --> 02:55.425
But the soul of what I do --
what gives me real joy --

02:55.425 --> 02:58.053
is this.

02:58.053 --> 03:02.557
And you built your empire
despite no formal education.

03:02.557 --> 03:04.393
I got to where I am
by not being afraid

03:04.393 --> 03:06.770
to get down on my hands
and knees.

03:06.770 --> 03:09.815
My blood and sweat,
they're in these vines.

03:09.815 --> 03:10.941
♪♪

03:10.941 --> 03:12.984
Hello.
My name Inigo Montoya.

03:12.984 --> 03:14.986
You kill my father.
Prepare to die.

03:18.365 --> 03:21.702
You killed my father.
Prepare to die.

03:21.702 --> 03:23.704
[ Chuckles ]

03:23.704 --> 03:26.748
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

03:30.293 --> 03:35.465
For you,
Princesssa Buttercup.

03:40.137 --> 03:41.555
[ Speaking Spanish ]

03:42.931 --> 03:45.016
<i>Oye,</i> Rosa.

03:45.016 --> 03:46.726
I like Lettie.

03:46.726 --> 03:48.145
[ Laughs ]

03:57.237 --> 04:03.410
♪♪

04:13.378 --> 04:15.046
♪♪

04:15.046 --> 04:19.301
If you care about her,
don't get in her way.

04:19.301 --> 04:23.096
She's meant to be more
than a grape picker.

04:23.096 --> 04:24.931
Can you say the same?

04:24.931 --> 04:30.604
♪♪

04:30.604 --> 04:32.481
Wine is boring.

04:32.481 --> 04:33.815
Wine is serious.

04:33.815 --> 04:36.443
Wine is snobby words like
"bouquet" and "acidity"

04:36.443 --> 04:37.944
that just shut people out.

04:37.944 --> 04:40.363
Wine is the rope line
at the club.

04:40.363 --> 04:41.740
But not Reina Rosada.

04:41.740 --> 04:44.826
Reina Rosada is the party that
everybody is invited to,

04:44.826 --> 04:46.912
and that's what we're selling --

04:46.912 --> 04:49.748
a good time
that tastes good.

04:51.416 --> 04:54.002
You guys clearly put
a lot of word into this.

04:55.712 --> 04:58.757
Which is what makes this
so hard.

04:58.757 --> 05:01.343
Wait -- Wait.
Are -- Are you passing?

05:01.343 --> 05:02.594
Veronica.

05:02.594 --> 05:05.013
Carmen, people in their 20s
drink beer, liquor,

05:05.013 --> 05:06.389
hard seltzers.

05:06.389 --> 05:08.058
We've discussed this,
and honestly, there was nothing

05:08.058 --> 05:10.268
in your pitch that changed
that one very simple

05:10.268 --> 05:12.395
demographic reality.

05:13.438 --> 05:14.773
So, that's it?
You're leaving?

05:14.773 --> 05:16.942
I'm running late for
the interview for Papa's award.

05:16.942 --> 05:19.236
Can you just make sure you drop
off Rita at the babysitter's?

05:19.236 --> 05:21.071
At least take my idea
to the board.

05:21.071 --> 05:23.031
Let them decide.

05:23.031 --> 05:27.327
I'm sorry, and have them
question my credibility?

05:27.327 --> 05:28.787
"Work with Michael,"
you said.

05:28.787 --> 05:30.247
All this time,
I thought it was Papi

05:30.247 --> 05:31.957
who was shutting me out,
but it was actually you.

05:33.500 --> 05:35.043
No one's shutting
you out.

05:35.043 --> 05:36.670
But I can't support
a bad idea

05:36.670 --> 05:38.630
simply because
it's my sister's bad idea.

05:38.630 --> 05:40.632
I'm sorry.

05:42.759 --> 05:45.762
Taste the clay.
We harvest in two weeks.

05:45.762 --> 05:47.764
[ Vehicles approaching ]

05:47.764 --> 05:50.267
♪♪

05:50.267 --> 05:51.977
Excuse me one moment.

05:51.977 --> 05:54.104
♪♪

05:54.104 --> 05:55.355
Can I help you?

05:55.355 --> 05:58.108
Officer Timms, Immigration
and Customs Enforcement.

05:58.108 --> 05:59.651
Are you Joe Sandoval?

05:59.651 --> 06:01.486
Joe.

06:01.486 --> 06:02.696
That's right.

06:02.696 --> 06:04.531
We're conducting random checks
throughout the Valley.

06:04.531 --> 06:06.992
Today? Oh, I usually get
a heads up.

06:06.992 --> 06:08.451
Can I speak to
your HR manager?

06:08.451 --> 06:09.995
We're going to need to see
I-9's.

06:09.995 --> 06:14.332
Of course. We comply fully
with all ICE regulations.

06:14.332 --> 06:16.793
Gonzo, Mateo's up
at the house.

06:16.793 --> 06:19.296
Will you let him know I'll be
late for our meeting?

06:19.296 --> 06:20.797
Understood, boss.

06:20.797 --> 06:22.465
[ Speaking Spanish ]

06:22.465 --> 06:23.550
♪♪

06:23.550 --> 06:25.385
So, how dressy is
this award thing tonight?

06:25.385 --> 06:26.636
You're not wearing that.

06:26.636 --> 06:27.721
Okay?
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

06:27.721 --> 06:30.473
Daniela, make sure
he looks nice, please.

06:30.473 --> 06:32.142
I think he looks nice
now.

06:32.142 --> 06:33.643
No, niña. No.

06:33.643 --> 06:34.811
[ Chuckles ]

06:34.811 --> 06:37.063
Oh, my God.
What is it?

06:37.063 --> 06:38.732
It's Gonzo.

06:38.732 --> 06:40.692
ICE is on the vineyard.

06:40.692 --> 06:43.612
♪♪

06:43.612 --> 06:45.322
Ma, come on, we have to get
Daniela out of here.

06:45.322 --> 06:48.033
Quick. I'll drive.

06:48.033 --> 06:51.036
[ Vehicle approaching ]

06:54.998 --> 06:56.166
Oh, no.

06:56.166 --> 06:57.709
Okay, just turn around,
turn around.

06:57.709 --> 06:58.918
Hey, lower your hand.

06:58.918 --> 07:01.129
Daniela, get on the floor.

07:01.129 --> 07:02.964
And don't at look them
in the eye, Mateo,

07:02.964 --> 07:04.341
but don't look away.

07:04.341 --> 07:05.759
Okay.
Just relax.

07:05.759 --> 07:07.052
What will we do
if they stop us?

07:07.052 --> 07:09.095
They're not gonna stop
this car.

07:09.095 --> 07:16.603
♪♪

07:16.603 --> 07:24.152
♪♪

07:24.152 --> 07:25.403
They're gonna sweep
the whole Valley.

07:25.403 --> 07:26.571
It's not safe at my place.

07:26.571 --> 07:28.114
So, where can we go?

07:28.114 --> 07:30.075
I know a place.

07:30.075 --> 07:31.076
♪♪

07:31.076 --> 07:33.078
Quick. Quick.

07:33.078 --> 07:43.004
♪♪

07:47.884 --> 07:49.552
Where did Lettie take them?

07:55.975 --> 08:05.819
♪♪

08:05.819 --> 08:08.446
Here's the files
you asked for.

08:08.446 --> 08:14.953
♪♪

08:14.953 --> 08:21.418
♪♪

08:21.418 --> 08:23.294
The bones are gone.

08:23.294 --> 08:24.421
I know.

08:24.421 --> 08:25.463
People are talking.

08:25.463 --> 08:27.716
The rumor's
all over the vineyard.

08:27.716 --> 08:29.426
So, who did you tell?

08:29.426 --> 08:32.095
Who did you tell, Javier?

08:32.095 --> 08:34.472
My father.
Gonzo.

08:34.472 --> 08:36.182
He wouldn't do anything
to hurt Joe.

08:36.182 --> 08:37.350
Maybe Flaco said something.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.018
But don't worry,
I'm gonna nip this in the bud.

08:39.018 --> 08:40.937
Don't.

08:40.937 --> 08:42.564
Let them talk.

08:42.564 --> 08:43.648
Why?

08:43.648 --> 08:44.983
I thought you wanted to protect
your father.

08:44.983 --> 08:46.109
Yeah, that was before
I found out

08:46.109 --> 08:47.360
that he murdered
my grandfather.

08:47.360 --> 08:50.822
If you think that Joe did it,
we should go to the cops.

08:50.822 --> 08:54.909
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:54.909 --> 08:56.661
If he's guilty,
he'll be punished.

08:56.661 --> 08:59.873
If he's not, he gets a chance to
clear his name.

08:59.873 --> 09:03.918
Just. Let. Them. Talk.

09:03.918 --> 09:06.129
♪♪

09:06.129 --> 09:08.339
This is Shakespearean,
Antonio.

09:08.339 --> 09:10.258
♪♪

09:10.258 --> 09:11.801
It'll come back
to haunt you.

09:11.801 --> 09:13.136
♪♪

09:13.136 --> 09:14.137
Don't do this.

09:14.137 --> 09:16.556
I'm not doing anything.

09:16.556 --> 09:21.311
I'm just letting the rumor mill
take its course.

09:21.311 --> 09:23.146
So are you.

09:23.146 --> 09:29.027
♪♪

09:29.027 --> 09:30.528
Ay!

09:34.240 --> 09:36.034
I like the hard work.

09:36.034 --> 09:39.037
That is how you get ahead
in this country!

09:39.037 --> 09:40.914
Ay!
[ Speaking Spanish ]

09:49.923 --> 09:52.092
Joe: Billy.
<i>¿Donde esta?</i>

09:52.092 --> 09:54.219
"Refrigerator".
Again.

09:54.219 --> 09:56.179
"Refrigerator."

10:12.237 --> 10:13.905
Honeycroft?

10:18.243 --> 10:21.121
♪ And groovin' was groovin' ♪

10:25.083 --> 10:27.877
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

10:29.921 --> 10:32.215
<i>Oye.</i>

10:50.108 --> 10:52.277
♪ Say yeah, yeah, yeah ♪

10:52.277 --> 10:58.449
♪♪

11:00.451 --> 11:02.912
♪♪

11:02.912 --> 11:04.998
Part of me thinks she's scared
I'll show her up.

11:04.998 --> 11:08.334
Like if Papi finally sees
how good I am,

11:08.334 --> 11:10.670
she'll have no room
to shine.

11:10.670 --> 11:12.755
Well, Veronica's always gotta be
the best at everything.

11:12.755 --> 11:14.299
[ Cork pops ]
To the detriment of
our relationship,

11:14.299 --> 11:15.925
and now, clearly, yours.

11:15.925 --> 11:18.344
Then, part of me wonders,
well,

11:18.344 --> 11:20.430
what if I think
I'm really good,

11:20.430 --> 11:21.890
but the truth is I'm not?

11:21.890 --> 11:23.308
[ Chuckles ]
Maybe I'm just fooling myself.

11:23.308 --> 11:25.268
Maybe I'm actually no good.

11:25.268 --> 11:26.936
Hey. Come on.

11:26.936 --> 11:28.563
You know that's not true.

11:28.563 --> 11:31.733
I don't care what V says,
you did a great job on this.

11:31.733 --> 11:34.152
♪♪

11:34.152 --> 11:35.987
[ Sighs ]

11:35.987 --> 11:36.988
♪♪

11:36.988 --> 11:39.824
[ Liquid pours ]

11:39.824 --> 11:43.536
♪♪

11:43.536 --> 11:45.038
To us.

11:45.038 --> 11:46.497
To us.

11:46.497 --> 11:51.044
♪♪

11:51.044 --> 11:52.503
[ Sighs ]

11:52.795 --> 11:54.839
Mara: Your father
just named you CEO

11:54.839 --> 11:56.591
of Heritage House Vineyards,

11:56.591 --> 11:58.885
a position that's only been held
by two men --

11:58.885 --> 12:01.429
your father and
Oscar Honeycroft.

12:01.429 --> 12:03.264
What's it like succeeding
two legends?

12:03.264 --> 12:05.183
Well, here's the reality.

12:05.183 --> 12:08.645
My father bent over
and picked grapes.

12:08.645 --> 12:11.022
He rolled up his sleeves
and got his hands dirty --

12:11.022 --> 12:12.649
he still does sometimes.

12:12.649 --> 12:14.776
He did the job that
most white people thought

12:14.776 --> 12:16.361
they were too good for.

12:16.361 --> 12:18.196
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

12:18.196 --> 12:19.197
♪♪

12:19.197 --> 12:21.991
Was that about Lettie?

12:21.991 --> 12:23.701
The old rumors are back.

12:25.453 --> 12:27.789
The vineyard workers
and the house staff, too.

12:27.789 --> 12:31.125
People are saying that they
found bones on the vineyard.

12:32.543 --> 12:33.836
That's not possible.

12:33.836 --> 12:35.922
That's not possible because
I didn't kill anyone.

12:35.922 --> 12:37.131
Don't take it out on me.

12:37.131 --> 12:38.591
I'm just your eyes
and ears.

12:38.591 --> 12:40.760
And those whispers
are getting louder.

12:40.760 --> 12:42.720
They're saying
"Joe killed the old man."

12:42.720 --> 12:48.101
♪♪

12:48.101 --> 12:53.523
♪♪

12:53.523 --> 12:55.275
I brought you some tea.

12:56.317 --> 12:58.444
[ Chuckles ]
It'll warm you up.

13:04.575 --> 13:06.911
[ Speaking Spanish ]

13:06.911 --> 13:08.746
<i>Gracias.</i>

13:10.957 --> 13:12.667
Oh, but this is nice.

13:12.667 --> 13:14.252
What is --

13:14.252 --> 13:18.381
It tastes like,
uh -- uh, toothpaste?

13:18.381 --> 13:20.800
It's mint.

13:20.800 --> 13:22.135
I never had it.

13:27.932 --> 13:31.602
♪♪

13:31.602 --> 13:34.314
You're quiet.

13:34.314 --> 13:36.816
My English not too good.

13:36.816 --> 13:38.276
Lettie teach me, <i>pero...</i>

13:38.276 --> 13:40.111
No, what I mean is...

13:40.111 --> 13:42.447
you don't say anything
unless you mean it.

13:42.447 --> 13:45.158
Billy loves to talk.
You're more of a thinker.

13:45.158 --> 13:48.119
[ Chuckles ]

13:48.119 --> 13:49.871
How do you like it here?

13:49.871 --> 13:52.999
In America, on the vineyard.

13:52.999 --> 13:55.710
I like.

13:55.710 --> 13:57.003
I love the vineyard.

13:57.003 --> 13:58.296
[ Chuckles ]

13:58.296 --> 14:00.048
The grapes.

14:00.048 --> 14:01.924
Working hard.

14:01.924 --> 14:06.387
♪♪

14:06.387 --> 14:11.934
But sometimes, I feel...

14:11.934 --> 14:13.644
<i>Ay. ¿Cómo se dice?</i>

14:13.644 --> 14:17.482
♪♪

14:17.482 --> 14:18.941
Alone.

14:18.941 --> 14:20.151
♪♪

14:20.151 --> 14:22.570
I know exactly
how you feel.

14:22.570 --> 14:24.405
You? [ Chuckles ]
No. Not you.

14:24.405 --> 14:25.823
I do.

14:25.823 --> 14:27.533
You see a big house.
I see a lot of room

14:27.533 --> 14:29.285
to be alone in.

14:29.285 --> 14:30.995
At least you have
a nice pillow

14:30.995 --> 14:32.288
and someone
to cook for you.

14:32.288 --> 14:34.373
[ Chuckles ] I'll cook for you
whenever you want.

14:34.373 --> 14:35.541
Really?
No.

14:35.541 --> 14:36.876
I'm a terrible cook.

14:36.876 --> 14:39.378
That's why we have Marta.
[ Chuckles ]

14:39.378 --> 14:43.049
But, uh...I'll heat up
some tea for you.

14:43.049 --> 14:44.592
[ Cup clacks ]

14:44.592 --> 14:47.303
♪♪

14:47.303 --> 14:50.306
You're not alone, Joe.
You have me.

14:50.306 --> 14:53.267
♪♪

14:53.267 --> 14:55.645
You're cold. Hey.

14:55.645 --> 14:57.396
Here you go.

14:59.565 --> 15:01.984
[ Footsteps approach ]

15:01.984 --> 15:03.402
Margaret!
[ Gasps ]

15:03.402 --> 15:04.445
♪♪

15:04.445 --> 15:05.822
What the hell is this?

15:05.822 --> 15:07.406
Daddy!
We weren't doing anything.

15:07.406 --> 15:08.741
Get in the house.
Daddy!

15:10.034 --> 15:11.577
What did you say?

15:16.374 --> 15:17.959
She's your daughter.

15:17.959 --> 15:19.418
Her word should be good enough
for you.

15:19.418 --> 15:21.003
[ Gasps ] Daddy!

15:21.003 --> 15:28.344
♪♪

15:28.344 --> 15:35.726
♪♪

15:35.726 --> 15:37.812
Reporter: <i>Immigration and</i>
<i>customs enforcement officials</i>

15:37.812 --> 15:39.397
<i>conducting a sweep of</i>
<i>the Sonoma Valley</i>

15:39.397 --> 15:41.399
<i>this afternoon.</i>
<i>These actions have become</i>

15:41.399 --> 15:42.859
<i>increasingly common</i>
<i>in recent years.</i>

15:42.859 --> 15:44.902
<i>As part of the operation,</i>
<i>ICE agents made</i>

15:44.902 --> 15:47.405
<i>at-large arrests at residences,</i>
<i>work sites, and traffic stops.</i>

15:47.405 --> 15:49.240
Can you turn this off?
I can't watch this anymore.

15:49.240 --> 15:50.741
How are they allowed
to do this?

15:50.741 --> 15:52.076
We need a plan.

15:52.076 --> 15:54.245
Mateo, once the raids are over,
Daniela's gonna be okay.

15:54.245 --> 15:55.371
Yeah, sure,
until next time.

15:55.371 --> 15:56.581
We can't live like this.

15:56.581 --> 15:57.790
How can anyone
live like this?

15:57.790 --> 15:59.208
We don't have a choice.

15:59.208 --> 16:01.294
This is how it is, Mateo!

16:01.294 --> 16:03.713
♪♪

16:03.713 --> 16:05.631
Yes, we do.

16:05.631 --> 16:12.972
♪♪

16:12.972 --> 16:15.224
Marry me, Daniela.

16:15.224 --> 16:16.976
Mateo, what...

16:16.976 --> 16:17.977
♪♪

16:17.977 --> 16:19.520
Marry me.

16:19.520 --> 16:21.564
I'm a citizen.

16:21.564 --> 16:22.899
This is the only way
to keep you safe.

16:22.899 --> 16:24.984
I can't lose you.

16:24.984 --> 16:26.944
I won't lose you.

16:26.944 --> 16:29.906
♪♪

16:29.906 --> 16:32.200
I love you.

16:32.200 --> 16:33.409
♪♪

16:33.409 --> 16:36.454
Lettie: Mateo...

16:36.454 --> 16:38.497
I love you.
You're my son.

16:38.497 --> 16:40.625
But you've lost your mind.

16:40.625 --> 16:47.340
♪♪

16:51.928 --> 16:57.475
♪♪

16:57.475 --> 17:03.356
♪♪

17:03.356 --> 17:05.233
Hey, Papito.

17:06.275 --> 17:07.401
Club soda?

17:07.401 --> 17:08.903
You know it.

17:09.946 --> 17:10.947
Where's Lettie?

17:10.947 --> 17:12.365
I don't know.
I texted her.

17:12.365 --> 17:13.991
Carmen and Mateo
aren't here, either.

17:13.991 --> 17:16.369
That's probably why Dad
looks so pissed.

17:16.369 --> 17:19.497
How are our friends
from Immigration?

17:19.497 --> 17:22.500
They're in HR, going through
our records now.

17:22.500 --> 17:23.918
We'll be fine.

17:23.918 --> 17:25.878
All of our workers
are documented.

17:25.878 --> 17:35.179
♪♪

17:35.179 --> 17:37.473
Hello, Joe.

17:39.141 --> 17:40.142
Where's Lettie?

17:40.142 --> 17:41.227
Margaret.

17:41.227 --> 17:44.021
Lettie got tied up.
She'll be here soon.

17:44.021 --> 17:45.231
I was just at the bar,

17:45.231 --> 17:47.191
and I heard
the most upsetting rumor.

17:47.191 --> 17:48.859
[ Scoffs ]
You know it's not true.

17:48.859 --> 17:51.571
I know I don't want it
to be true, but...

17:51.571 --> 17:53.656
that's not the same thing,
is it?

17:53.656 --> 17:55.658
♪♪

17:55.658 --> 17:57.618
[ Sighs ]

17:57.618 --> 18:03.541
♪♪

18:03.541 --> 18:05.167
Sorry about earlier.

18:05.167 --> 18:07.003
♪♪

18:07.003 --> 18:09.171
Don't worry.
My father went into town.

18:11.632 --> 18:13.843
He shouldn't treat you
that way.

18:13.843 --> 18:16.012
He loves me.
He's just...

18:16.012 --> 18:18.681
overprotective
since my mom died.

18:19.974 --> 18:22.143
Here.

18:25.813 --> 18:27.732
The way you stood up to him,
no one's ever done anything

18:27.732 --> 18:29.483
like that for me before.

18:31.402 --> 18:34.071
Is it helping?

18:42.663 --> 18:44.749
Margaret --
I know, Joe.

18:44.749 --> 18:46.000
♪♪

18:46.000 --> 18:48.085
I know you love her.

18:48.085 --> 18:49.170
♪♪

18:49.170 --> 18:51.422
She doesn't know,
does she?

18:51.964 --> 18:53.382
You had the courage to stand up
to my father,

18:53.382 --> 18:56.260
but you can't find the courage
to tell Lettie how you feel.

18:56.260 --> 18:59.013
[ Speaks Spanish ]

18:59.013 --> 19:01.390
I'm too scared.

19:01.390 --> 19:03.392
What's more scary,

19:03.392 --> 19:06.562
telling her or losing her?

19:06.562 --> 19:08.189
You should tell her, Joe.

19:08.189 --> 19:10.316
Now, before it's too late.

19:10.316 --> 19:11.442
[ Sniffs ]

19:13.152 --> 19:15.154
Okay.

19:18.574 --> 19:20.826
<i>Oye.</i>

19:23.954 --> 19:26.082
Even I understand
what that means.

19:26.082 --> 19:29.085
♪♪

19:29.085 --> 19:31.545
Joe, wait.

19:31.545 --> 19:32.588
♪♪

19:32.588 --> 19:35.091
Earlier today,
I saw, um...

19:35.091 --> 19:38.636
♪♪

19:38.636 --> 19:40.262
Nothing.

19:40.262 --> 19:42.056
Be careful out there.

19:42.056 --> 19:50.773
♪♪

19:50.773 --> 19:59.490
♪♪

19:59.490 --> 20:08.165
♪♪

20:08.165 --> 20:10.835
This is nice.

20:10.835 --> 20:15.965
My abuela gave it to me
before I left El Salvador.

20:15.965 --> 20:18.634
She told me
to wear it always.

20:18.634 --> 20:20.302
Who is it?

20:20.302 --> 20:22.763
Saint Romo.

20:22.763 --> 20:25.558
He appeared to a man who was
lost in the desert.

20:25.558 --> 20:27.977
He's the patron saint
of immigrants.

20:27.977 --> 20:29.645
I never heard of him.

20:29.645 --> 20:33.691
You never had a reason to.

20:33.691 --> 20:36.861
Your family is never going
to accept me, Mateo.

20:36.861 --> 20:39.363
Forget my family,
Daniela.

20:39.363 --> 20:41.365
♪♪

20:41.365 --> 20:44.034
I want you
to be my family.

20:44.034 --> 20:45.494
♪♪

20:45.494 --> 20:48.038
Daniela, please.

20:48.038 --> 20:51.000
♪♪

20:51.000 --> 20:55.254
If your mother gives me
her blessing, I'll marry you.

20:55.254 --> 20:56.338
Okay.

20:56.338 --> 21:01.469
♪♪

21:01.469 --> 21:03.679
Then I'm gonna get
her blessing.

21:03.679 --> 21:09.685
♪♪

21:09.685 --> 21:15.691
♪♪

21:15.691 --> 21:16.901
[ Latin music playing ]

21:23.741 --> 21:25.409
♪♪

21:27.787 --> 21:29.997
I love it here.

21:31.957 --> 21:33.834
I love it here, too.

21:36.337 --> 21:37.546
[ Chuckles ]

21:37.546 --> 21:40.382
I'm going to buy you big cars
and fancy dresses.

21:41.425 --> 21:44.094
We're going to eat together at
the fanciest restaurants.

21:44.094 --> 21:45.805
<i>¿Sí?</i>
<i>Sí.</i>

21:45.805 --> 21:47.056
So...

21:48.891 --> 21:51.227
[ Speaking Spanish ]

21:51.227 --> 21:53.938
♪♪

22:00.861 --> 22:02.404
I'm sorry, Lettie.

22:15.918 --> 22:19.672
♪♪

22:26.512 --> 22:29.265
♪♪

22:37.898 --> 22:41.151
Lettie... Leticia...
Lettie...

22:41.151 --> 22:43.529
Lettie: [ Giggling ]

22:43.529 --> 22:47.616
♪♪

22:47.616 --> 22:49.535
[ Laughter ]

22:49.535 --> 22:55.583
♪♪

22:59.879 --> 23:01.630
I don't know. The thing is,
you're the one that's --

23:01.630 --> 23:02.631
I'm used to it.
Well, yeah.

23:02.631 --> 23:03.716
No, it's just maddening
to me

23:03.716 --> 23:05.175
that she doesn't see
your talent.

23:05.175 --> 23:07.094
Me?
Yeah.

23:07.094 --> 23:09.430
What about you? She treats you
like a babysitter,

23:09.430 --> 23:11.432
questions what you spend,
where you go.

23:12.725 --> 23:14.351
She doesn't appreciate you.

23:16.896 --> 23:18.814
Well, hey, we should probably
get going.

23:18.814 --> 23:20.399
Going where?

23:20.399 --> 23:22.526
Your father's award thing.
It starts in, like, an hour.

23:22.526 --> 23:23.944
Yeah, I'm not --
I'm not going to that.

23:23.944 --> 23:26.864
Mm. Carmen.
Come on. You have to.

23:26.864 --> 23:28.699
No. Screw them.

23:28.699 --> 23:30.576
My family doesn't care
about me.

23:30.576 --> 23:33.120
I could disappear right now,

23:33.120 --> 23:35.539
and they wouldn't even
notice.

23:35.998 --> 23:37.666
I would.

23:39.877 --> 23:41.003
Mm.

23:41.003 --> 23:42.338
♪♪

23:42.338 --> 23:43.839
Mm. Hey, hey.

23:43.839 --> 23:45.007
What are you doing?

23:45.007 --> 23:47.718
I'm -- I'm sorry.
I don't --

23:47.718 --> 23:51.388
I don't -- I don't know why
I did that.

23:51.388 --> 23:52.473
I'm sorry.

23:52.473 --> 23:54.099
Yeah.

23:54.099 --> 23:58.103
♪♪

24:06.570 --> 24:09.073
I'm so sorry.

24:10.991 --> 24:14.328
I feel so stupid.

24:16.121 --> 24:17.957
If V ever found out...

24:17.957 --> 24:21.710
[ Grae's "Bang Bang" plays ]

24:21.710 --> 24:23.671
I've always wanted you.

24:23.671 --> 24:24.797
♪♪

24:24.797 --> 24:26.882
♪ Told me you were drowning ♪

24:26.882 --> 24:29.218
♪ Warned me when you found me ♪

24:29.218 --> 24:32.596
♪ I sank right into you ♪

24:32.596 --> 24:34.181
♪ Yeah ♪

24:34.181 --> 24:37.101
[ Laughter,
indistinct conversations ]

24:37.101 --> 24:39.186
♪♪

24:39.186 --> 24:40.229
Come on, Joe.

24:40.229 --> 24:42.022
The statute of limitations
has passed.

24:42.022 --> 24:44.358
Where did you bury
Old Honeycroft's body?

24:44.358 --> 24:45.943
Wait, haven't you heard,
Steve?

24:45.943 --> 24:47.361
The bones
are on the move.

24:47.361 --> 24:48.779
Yeah.

24:48.779 --> 24:51.657
Look, Joe.
We get it.

24:51.657 --> 24:53.701
How else were you supposed to
get ahead?

24:53.701 --> 24:54.910
[ Laughter ]
[ Clears throat ]

24:54.910 --> 24:56.286
Excuse me.

24:56.286 --> 24:58.455
Gentlemen,
may I borrow Joe for a sec?

24:58.455 --> 25:00.582
♪♪

25:00.582 --> 25:03.502
Well, if we can borrow you
at some point?

25:03.502 --> 25:06.088
[ Laughter ]

25:09.049 --> 25:10.718
Why are you letting them talk
to you like that?

25:10.718 --> 25:12.469
It's a joke, Veronica.

25:12.469 --> 25:14.179
A bad joke,
but I can take it.

25:14.179 --> 25:15.764
Yeah, well,
you shouldn't have to.

25:15.764 --> 25:18.350
<i>Mira,</i>
ego is for white people.

25:18.350 --> 25:21.103
Sure, you see them making
a joke at my expense.

25:21.103 --> 25:22.604
It makes them feel good.

25:22.604 --> 25:25.607
I hang my head,
I let them laugh,

25:25.607 --> 25:27.818
but at the end of the day,
I get their business,

25:27.818 --> 25:29.361
and I take their money.

25:29.361 --> 25:31.030
That joke cost me nothing.

25:31.030 --> 25:32.990
It cost them millions.

25:32.990 --> 25:34.867
Fine.

25:34.867 --> 25:36.618
Then give me a number.
Hmm?

25:36.618 --> 25:38.162
How much should I sell
my ass for?

25:38.162 --> 25:40.622
'Cause that's all those men
care about out there.

25:40.622 --> 25:42.666
But, hey, as long
as I'm taking their money,

25:42.666 --> 25:43.834
that's all that matters,
right?

25:43.834 --> 25:45.169
Don't talk to me
that way.

25:45.169 --> 25:46.712
Why not?

25:46.712 --> 25:49.631
You just let them do it.

25:49.631 --> 25:54.762
♪♪

26:03.145 --> 26:06.023
You know I can't live
without her.

26:06.815 --> 26:10.194
Please, Ama.
Just give us your blessing.

26:13.280 --> 26:16.075
I'm sorry.

26:16.075 --> 26:18.077
I'm sorry, <i>mi amor,</i>
but I can't do that.

26:18.077 --> 26:19.286
Why?

26:19.286 --> 26:21.163
Because she's not rich?
Because she's undocumented?

26:21.163 --> 26:23.373
No, no, no, no, no.
<i>Eso no es.</i>

26:23.373 --> 26:25.292
Well, then why?
Tell me.

26:28.128 --> 26:34.426
My sister Rosa and I,
we came to this country

26:34.426 --> 26:37.846
because...

26:37.846 --> 26:40.682
it didn't matter
who you were.

26:40.682 --> 26:45.687
It didn't matter
where you came from.

26:47.898 --> 26:50.901
You could be anything.

26:50.901 --> 26:53.403
I wanted that for me,

26:53.403 --> 26:55.739
and I wanted that
for my children.

26:55.739 --> 26:57.699
♪♪

26:57.699 --> 27:00.077
And I gave you that.

27:00.077 --> 27:01.078
♪♪

27:01.078 --> 27:02.412
And of everything
I've done,

27:02.412 --> 27:06.083
that's the one thing
that I am the most proud of.

27:06.083 --> 27:07.334
And I am grateful.

27:07.334 --> 27:09.419
I really am, Ma.

27:09.419 --> 27:11.463
But what does this have to do
with me getting married?

27:11.463 --> 27:14.424
Right now, you are free.

27:14.424 --> 27:18.053
You can be whoever you want,
do whatever you want.

27:18.053 --> 27:20.389
If you marry Daniela,
that is over.

27:20.389 --> 27:22.808
Oh, that's ridiculous.
No, it isn't!

27:22.808 --> 27:24.726
You'll always have to think of
someone else.

27:24.726 --> 27:26.937
Believe me, I know.

27:26.937 --> 27:27.938
You don't.

27:27.938 --> 27:29.606
This is about
you and Joe.

27:29.606 --> 27:31.900
This is about you giving up
your dreams for him.

27:31.900 --> 27:33.569
But that was your choice.

27:33.569 --> 27:37.030
No one made you do it.
Not even him.

27:37.030 --> 27:38.615
♪♪

27:38.615 --> 27:40.659
I'm sorry.

27:40.659 --> 27:41.994
♪♪

27:41.994 --> 27:43.745
Mateo.

27:43.745 --> 27:48.834
♪♪

27:48.834 --> 27:53.881
♪♪

27:53.881 --> 27:55.924
To some, he was CEO.

27:55.924 --> 27:59.845
To others, stiff competition.

27:59.845 --> 28:02.723
Mexican-American.
<i>Inmigrante.</i>

28:03.891 --> 28:06.101
Trailblazer.

28:06.101 --> 28:08.186
To me, the word
that matters most

28:08.186 --> 28:10.856
and defines him -- Papa.

28:10.856 --> 28:13.191
Ladies and gentlemen,
it is a pleasure

28:13.191 --> 28:17.112
to introduce to you
the man who taught me

28:17.112 --> 28:19.197
that no one is better
than me

28:19.197 --> 28:22.242
and that I could be
anything,

28:22.242 --> 28:23.493
Joe Sandoval.

28:23.493 --> 28:26.538
[ Applause ]

28:36.798 --> 28:39.801
[ Applause stops ]

28:51.438 --> 28:53.690
It's an amazing thing.

28:53.690 --> 28:55.567
A kid from the middle of
nowhere,

28:55.567 --> 28:58.195
no money, no education,
comes to this country

28:58.195 --> 29:00.197
and builds an empire.

29:00.197 --> 29:02.282
Doesn't seem possible.

29:02.282 --> 29:04.868
Or at least to some of you,
it doesn't.

29:04.868 --> 29:09.706
A brown man,
building all this?

29:09.706 --> 29:12.417
He must have done something.

29:12.417 --> 29:14.503
He must have committed murder.

29:14.503 --> 29:16.380
[ Murmuring ]

29:16.380 --> 29:18.006
I get why many of you
want to believe

29:18.006 --> 29:20.759
I killed Oscar Honeycroft.

29:20.759 --> 29:23.512
If you didn't, how could
you sleep at night?

29:23.512 --> 29:25.180
You'd be too embarrassed.

29:25.180 --> 29:27.516
I'd be embarrassed, too,
knowing that someone

29:27.516 --> 29:29.851
who started with nothing
could achieve more

29:29.851 --> 29:33.188
than I ever dreamed of.

29:34.815 --> 29:36.233
Right, Wayne?

29:36.233 --> 29:38.485
Wayne didn't have to work hard
to get to the top,

29:38.485 --> 29:41.071
because his father handed him
his business

29:41.071 --> 29:43.365
when he bombed out of college.

29:43.365 --> 29:44.908
What about you, Ron?

29:44.908 --> 29:48.578
Your company was twice as big
as mine when I started.

29:48.578 --> 29:51.081
How'd that work out?

29:51.081 --> 29:53.709
I guess it makes you wonder,

29:53.709 --> 29:55.836
what does this say about you
if someone like me

29:55.836 --> 29:59.881
could achieve what you couldn't?

29:59.881 --> 30:04.386
If I'm not a murderer,
then you're a fool.

30:04.386 --> 30:08.724
I'm not gonna call you a racist.
Even a clown knows what he is.

30:08.724 --> 30:12.769
But the facts are the facts,
and the fact is some of you

30:12.769 --> 30:15.188
are mad because even with
all that white privilege,

30:15.188 --> 30:19.568
you're still just
middle of the road.

30:19.568 --> 30:21.403
Me and mine?

30:21.403 --> 30:24.614
We've made ourselves smaller
for you.

30:24.614 --> 30:29.202
We're done breaking our backs
to make you feel worthy.

30:29.202 --> 30:33.165
So, to the Sandovals.

30:33.165 --> 30:37.753
We're not just taking
a slice this time.

30:37.753 --> 30:40.589
We're taking the whole damn pie.

30:40.589 --> 30:43.258
♪♪

30:43.258 --> 30:46.261
[ Clapping slowly ]

30:46.261 --> 30:49.264
[ Applause ]

30:49.264 --> 30:52.267
[ Whistling ]

30:52.267 --> 30:56.063
♪♪

31:00.984 --> 31:02.319
I wonder how much
that's going to cost me.

31:04.154 --> 31:05.864
Mm.
Worth every cent.

31:05.864 --> 31:07.449
That was dope, Pa.

31:07.449 --> 31:09.284
♪♪

31:09.284 --> 31:11.453
Powerful stuff.
I'm proud of you, Apa.

31:11.453 --> 31:13.080
♪♪

31:13.080 --> 31:14.331
You know,
for a minute there,

31:14.331 --> 31:15.916
I remembered why
I fell in love with you

31:15.916 --> 31:17.000
in the first place.

31:17.000 --> 31:18.710
Margaret,
I didn't do it.

31:18.710 --> 31:20.796
I know, Joe.

31:20.796 --> 31:22.839
♪♪

31:22.839 --> 31:24.091
I know.

31:24.091 --> 31:25.967
♪♪

31:25.967 --> 31:27.636
Voicemail: <i>Hello, you've reached</i>
<i>Joe Sandoval.</i>

31:27.636 --> 31:30.305
<i>Sorry I missed your c--</i>
[ Cellphone beeps ]

31:30.305 --> 31:31.807
Ah.

31:36.311 --> 31:38.355
Lettie.

31:38.355 --> 31:40.190
The next decision you make
could affect

31:40.190 --> 31:42.692
the rest of your life.

31:42.692 --> 31:45.445
You think
I don't know that?

31:45.445 --> 31:48.406
Mateo is the man he is today
because of you.

31:48.406 --> 31:52.035
You've been his mother,
his father, his everything.

31:52.035 --> 31:55.872
And that's what
he's become to you.

31:55.872 --> 31:57.374
You've got him this far.

31:57.374 --> 32:00.043
The rest he's gonna have to do
on his own.

32:02.963 --> 32:05.090
I know, Billy.

32:06.007 --> 32:07.467
But I'm scared.

32:07.467 --> 32:10.178
♪♪

32:10.178 --> 32:12.556
For him, for me.

32:12.556 --> 32:15.517
♪♪

32:15.517 --> 32:17.853
I know.

32:17.853 --> 32:22.232
But no matter what happens,
we'll get through it.

32:22.232 --> 32:24.067
Together.

32:24.067 --> 32:31.199
♪♪

32:31.199 --> 32:38.373
♪♪

32:38.373 --> 32:45.463
♪♪

32:45.463 --> 32:49.384
Billy:
Love is patient, love is kind.

32:49.384 --> 32:55.599
It does not envy, it does not
boast, it is not proud.

32:55.599 --> 32:58.226
Love does not
dishonor others.

32:58.226 --> 33:02.480
It is not self-seeking,
it is not quick to anger,

33:02.480 --> 33:05.609
it keeps no record of wrongs.

33:05.609 --> 33:11.573
Love does not delight in evil,
but rejoices in the truth.

33:11.573 --> 33:18.121
Love always protects,
always trusts, always hopes,

33:18.121 --> 33:20.916
always perseveres.

33:20.916 --> 33:28.882
♪♪

33:28.882 --> 33:31.384
Hey.
You're unbelievable.

33:31.384 --> 33:33.303
What?

33:33.303 --> 33:34.721
Don't you feel bad?

33:34.721 --> 33:36.640
Don't you feel anything?

33:36.640 --> 33:37.974
You know, not everything's
as black and white

33:37.974 --> 33:38.975
as you think it is.

33:38.975 --> 33:41.019
No, Javier, please.

33:41.019 --> 33:43.146
About my father,
about my family,

33:43.146 --> 33:45.815
about this company,
about why I'm here --

33:45.815 --> 33:48.276
it's messy,
and it's complicated,

33:48.276 --> 33:50.695
and sometimes,
I don't even know myself.

33:50.695 --> 33:51.821
All I know is that
you're the only person

33:51.821 --> 33:54.658
that I want to
talk to about it.

33:54.658 --> 33:56.534
About anything.

33:56.534 --> 33:58.495
♪♪

33:58.495 --> 34:00.664
Joe is a good man.

34:01.706 --> 34:05.627
He gave me the opportunity
to be a GM here.

34:05.627 --> 34:07.420
And I'm ashamed that I had
anything to do

34:07.420 --> 34:08.672
with poisoning
his reputation.
Oh, Javi --

34:08.672 --> 34:11.633
No, Antonio. No.

34:11.633 --> 34:15.428
Antonio.

34:15.428 --> 34:18.098
I thought
I owed you something

34:18.098 --> 34:21.977
because of how
I hurt you before.

34:21.977 --> 34:24.437
I'm not playing your games.

34:24.437 --> 34:25.605
Hey, Javier, wait --

34:25.605 --> 34:27.232
Don't touch me!
[ Scoffs ]

34:27.232 --> 34:29.359
I see you found
your backbone.

34:29.359 --> 34:30.819
Hmm?

34:30.819 --> 34:33.029
Where was this guy
10 years ago, huh?

34:33.029 --> 34:36.408
♪♪

34:36.408 --> 34:39.869
[ Estereromance's
"Dung Ding Dang" plays ]

34:39.869 --> 34:46.960
♪♪

34:46.960 --> 34:49.170
Oh, wait, wait.

34:50.422 --> 34:55.176
What? What?
What are you doing?

34:55.176 --> 34:57.137
You don't want to watch it
later?

34:57.137 --> 34:59.097
When I'm not here?

34:59.097 --> 35:05.270
♪ Se revela un enigma en me ♪

35:05.270 --> 35:11.818
♪ Tu espíritu canta así ♪

35:11.818 --> 35:13.653
♪ Dung ding dang ♪

35:13.653 --> 35:16.656
[ Water sloshing ]

35:16.656 --> 35:17.907
♪♪

35:17.907 --> 35:19.909
♪ Dung ding dang ♪

35:19.909 --> 35:22.245
♪ Dao dao ♪

35:22.245 --> 35:24.414
Oh.

35:24.414 --> 35:25.415
Are you kidding me?

35:25.415 --> 35:26.416
No --
V --

35:26.416 --> 35:27.709
How dare you?

35:27.709 --> 35:29.294
Get out!

35:29.294 --> 35:31.588
Okay.
Get out!

35:31.588 --> 35:33.715
Get out!

35:33.715 --> 35:35.717
♪♪

35:35.717 --> 35:37.177
[ Ring clatters ]

35:37.177 --> 35:39.346
[ Hyperventilating ]

35:43.892 --> 35:46.686
[ Crickets chirping ]

36:02.410 --> 36:04.537
[ Gate rattles ]

36:04.537 --> 36:07.707
[ The Cure's
"A Night Like This" plays ]

36:07.707 --> 36:16.758
♪♪

36:16.758 --> 36:18.259
[ Clattering ]

36:18.259 --> 36:20.261
♪ Say goodbye
on a night like this ♪

36:20.261 --> 36:22.430
♪ If it's the last thing
we ever do ♪

36:22.430 --> 36:24.140
Joe?

36:24.140 --> 36:25.892
♪ You never looked... ♪

36:25.892 --> 36:27.686
Are you crazy?

36:27.686 --> 36:29.854
Yes.

36:29.854 --> 36:32.524
Come here.

36:32.524 --> 36:35.610
♪ I'm coming to find you
if it takes me all night ♪

36:35.610 --> 36:36.903
[ Both laugh ]

36:36.903 --> 36:38.196
Shh.

36:38.196 --> 36:39.322
Shh.

36:39.322 --> 36:41.449
♪♪

36:41.449 --> 36:44.244
What did Lettie say?
[ Chuckles ]

36:44.244 --> 36:46.329
Forget Lettie.

36:46.329 --> 36:49.124
I don't love her.

36:49.124 --> 36:52.293
What changed?

36:52.293 --> 36:54.504
♪ For always and ever
is always for you ♪

36:54.504 --> 36:57.173
Us.

36:57.173 --> 36:59.634
There's an us?

37:01.136 --> 37:06.516
♪ Oh-ho-ho,
I want to change it all ♪

37:06.516 --> 37:09.227
♪♪

37:09.227 --> 37:13.398
♪ Oh-ho-ho, I want to change ♪

37:13.398 --> 37:17.068
♪♪

37:17.068 --> 37:20.905
♪ Oh-ho-ho, I want to change ♪

37:20.905 --> 37:26.411
♪♪

37:30.749 --> 37:32.333
I was just thinking.

37:32.333 --> 37:34.169
Mm-hmm?

37:36.212 --> 37:38.631
What could have been
between us.

37:40.759 --> 37:44.053
What we would have become.

37:44.053 --> 37:53.688
♪♪

37:53.688 --> 37:56.149
Did I say something?

37:56.149 --> 37:58.568
No. You're good.

37:58.568 --> 38:01.362
Where's my shirt?

38:01.362 --> 38:03.156
Antonio, stop.

38:03.156 --> 38:04.532
Hey, Antonio.
What?

38:04.532 --> 38:06.242
What now?

38:06.242 --> 38:08.578
You're responsible
for what we lost.

38:08.578 --> 38:10.038
You threw it away.

38:10.038 --> 38:11.623
I already apologized.

38:11.623 --> 38:13.249
I don't know what else
you want me to do.

38:13.249 --> 38:14.709
Nothing.

38:14.709 --> 38:16.252
Look, I'm sorry, Javi.

38:16.252 --> 38:18.004
This was nice.

38:18.004 --> 38:19.547
♪♪

38:19.547 --> 38:21.800
It doesn't really change
anything between us.

38:21.800 --> 38:27.472
♪♪

38:30.016 --> 38:32.936
[ Door opens, closes ]

38:32.936 --> 38:37.106
Veronica: If I were you,
I'd just listen and say yes.

38:37.106 --> 38:39.859
Or we can make this really,
really difficult.

38:40.819 --> 38:43.947
I'm filing for divorce.

38:43.947 --> 38:46.991
You'll no longer have access
to our bank accounts.

38:46.991 --> 38:49.702
And I'm keeping the house
and your car,

38:49.702 --> 38:52.664
both of which I paid for.

38:52.664 --> 38:54.707
And obviously, filing
for full custody of Rita.

38:54.707 --> 38:56.918
Hmm.
And what do I get?

38:56.918 --> 38:58.127
Your name.

38:58.127 --> 39:01.005
[ Chuckles ] Funny.

39:01.005 --> 39:04.717
But, uh, our prenup
says different.

39:07.095 --> 39:10.014
Our prenup says
that if we get divorced,

39:10.014 --> 39:15.937
I get $5 million and half of
your Heritage House stock.

39:15.937 --> 39:18.481
Oh, Michael.

39:18.481 --> 39:21.442
I may have been blindsided
by your betrayal,

39:21.442 --> 39:23.736
but at least I read
the fine print.

39:25.530 --> 39:27.365
You forfeit everything
if you engage in sex

39:27.365 --> 39:28.741
outside of the marriage.

39:28.741 --> 39:30.743
I didn't engage in sex
outside the marriage.

39:30.743 --> 39:33.580
Well, I sure hope the judge
agrees with you

39:33.580 --> 39:34.956
when she sees this.

39:34.956 --> 39:36.374
<i>[ Moaning ]</i>

39:36.374 --> 39:39.294
<i>[ Smooching ]</i>

39:39.961 --> 39:42.130
I knew about the money
you stole

39:42.130 --> 39:44.507
and the sex parties.

39:44.507 --> 39:46.092
Now I have proof.

39:46.092 --> 39:51.055
♪♪

39:51.055 --> 39:52.765
Veronica --
I'm done.

39:52.765 --> 39:59.856
♪♪

39:59.856 --> 40:01.900
[ Liquid pours ]

40:01.900 --> 40:03.860
♪♪

40:03.860 --> 40:05.153
[ Door opens ]

40:05.153 --> 40:08.239
♪♪

40:08.239 --> 40:09.490
[ Door closes ]

40:09.490 --> 40:14.829
♪♪

40:14.829 --> 40:20.126
♪♪

40:20.126 --> 40:22.045
I owe you.

40:22.045 --> 40:23.129
♪♪

40:23.129 --> 40:25.340
Yeah. You do.

40:25.340 --> 40:27.008
♪♪

40:27.008 --> 40:32.138
Hey, V, it was my idea.

40:32.138 --> 40:33.431
Yeah.

40:33.431 --> 40:35.850
God help the man
who messes with my sister.

40:35.850 --> 40:40.313
♪♪

40:40.313 --> 40:41.397
To us.

40:41.397 --> 40:42.941
To our future, baby.

40:42.941 --> 40:45.151
♪♪

40:45.151 --> 40:47.028
Here, eat a little more
before you go.

40:47.028 --> 40:48.696
Alright, no, no, no.
I'm so full.

40:48.696 --> 40:50.782
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

40:50.782 --> 40:52.533
<i>Gracias.</i>
Okay.

40:52.533 --> 40:53.534
[ Speaking Spanish ]

40:53.534 --> 40:54.786
Yeah, yeah.

40:54.786 --> 40:57.413
♪♪

40:57.413 --> 40:59.624
Hey.

40:59.624 --> 41:02.335
Until I can get you
a proper wedding present.

41:02.335 --> 41:04.045
♪♪

41:04.045 --> 41:06.547
Take it. Take it.

41:06.547 --> 41:08.132
Thank you.

41:08.132 --> 41:10.551
How long
will you be away?

41:10.551 --> 41:12.845
Hopefully it doesn't take
too long to apply for the visa,

41:12.845 --> 41:15.598
but Mateo will be back
next week.

41:15.598 --> 41:17.392
He wanted to stay
in El Salvador,

41:17.392 --> 41:21.396
but I'm making him come back
for the harvest.

41:21.396 --> 41:24.774
Take care, Daniela.

41:24.774 --> 41:27.610
Thank you, Mrs. Sandoval.

41:27.610 --> 41:28.945
♪♪

41:28.945 --> 41:30.571
We gotta go.

41:30.571 --> 41:32.615
One day, I'll pay
for a nicer honeymoon.

41:32.615 --> 41:34.534
Why?
I have everything I need, Ma.

41:34.534 --> 41:36.327
Oh, when did you
become a man?

41:36.327 --> 41:38.162
What is this?

41:38.162 --> 41:39.622
♪♪

41:39.622 --> 41:41.541
Go. Go, go, go.

41:41.541 --> 41:42.583
Let's go.

41:42.583 --> 41:44.502
Let's go.

41:44.502 --> 41:45.920
[ Chuckles ]

41:45.920 --> 41:47.755
♪♪

41:47.755 --> 41:49.382
Joe:
<i>It's an amazing thing.</i>

41:49.382 --> 41:51.134
[ Door opens ]

41:51.134 --> 41:54.929
<i>...no money, no education,</i>
<i>comes to this country...</i>

41:54.929 --> 41:57.974
Gonzo: I did what
you told me, boss.

41:57.974 --> 41:59.976
♪♪

41:59.976 --> 42:03.271
<i>Doesn't seem possible.</i>

42:03.271 --> 42:06.274
<i>Or to some of you, it doesn't.</i>

42:06.274 --> 42:08.401
♪♪

42:08.401 --> 42:13.114
<i>A brown man building all this?</i>

42:13.114 --> 42:15.783
You sure no one saw
you move them?

42:17.410 --> 42:19.412
<i>Must have done something.</i>

42:19.412 --> 42:21.414
<i>He must have committed murder.</i>

42:21.414 --> 42:24.625
♪♪
